ğŸ“˜ PROJECT OVERVIEW
-------------------
The Cinema Ticket Booking System is a console-based Java application built using Hibernate ORM instead of JDBC.

It allows administrators to manage movies and shows.
Customers can view seat availability, book tickets, make payments, and cancel bookings.

The project demonstrates real-time database interaction using Hibernate, covering:
	â€¢	ğŸ§© ORM mapping using JPA annotations
	â€¢	ğŸ”— Entity relationships (One-to-Many, Many-to-One, One-to-One)
	â€¢	ğŸ§  Lazy vs. Eager loading
	â€¢	ğŸ§® HQL queries & Criteria API
	â€¢	ğŸ’¾ Transaction management with Hibernate
	â€¢	ğŸ” Optimistic locking using @Version
	â€¢	ğŸ—ƒï¸ First-level & Second-level caching
	â€¢	ğŸ§» Soft deletes instead of physical deletes
	â€¢	ğŸ•’ Auto timestamps using @CreationTimestamp & @UpdateTimestamp
------------------------------------------------------

