ğŸï¸ MODULE 1: MOVIES & SHOWS MANAGEMENT
---------------------------------------
ğŸ¯ Objective:
Allow the admin to add movies and schedule shows in available auditoriums.

ğŸ§± Hibernate Entities:
	â€¢	Movie
	â€¢	Fields: id, title, language, duration, certification, status, createdAt , createdBy
	â€¢	Mapping: @Entity, @OneToMany(mappedBy="movie")

	â€¢	Auditorium
	â€¢	Fields: id, name, seatRows, seatCols
	â€¢	Mapping: @Entity

		â€¢	Auditorium_Properties
    	â€¢	Fields: id, screen_type, sound
    	â€¢	Mapping: @Entity

	â€¢	Show
	â€¢	Fields: id, movie, auditorium, showTime, endTime, status

	â€¢	Mapping:
	â€¢	@ManyToOne Movie
	â€¢	@ManyToOne Auditorium
	â€¢	@Version for concurrency

âœ… Use Case 1: Add Movie
Admin adds a new movie to the catalog.
Steps:
	1.	Admin enters movie details (title, language, duration, certification).
	2.	Hibernate HQL checks if movie already exists.
	3.	Insert into Movie table via session.persist(movie).

ğŸ§  Hibernate Concepts: JPA Annotations,HQL queries,Persisting entity objects,Soft delete using status field

âœ… Use Case 2: Create Show
Admin schedules a new show for a movie.
Steps:
	1.	Select movie & auditorium (Hibernate fetch).
	2.	Enter show date/time.
	3.	Check overlapping shows using HQL.
	4.	Persist show entity.

ğŸ§  Hibernate Concepts: @ManyToOne relationship,HQL time comparisons,Transaction handling

------------------------------------------------------

ğŸª‘ MODULE 2: SEAT BOOKING
--------------------------
ğŸ¯ Objective:
Allow customers to view seat availability and make ticket bookings.

ğŸ§± Hibernate Entities:
	â€¢	Seat
	â€¢	ShowSeat
	â€¢	Booking
	â€¢	BookingItem

âœ… Use Case 1: View Seat Availability
Customer views seats for a particular show.
Steps:
	1.	Enter show_id.
	2.	Fetch all ShowSeat records for that show.
	3.	Display seat map (AVAILABLE/BOOKED).

ğŸ§  Hibernate Concepts: HQL JOIN FETCH,Lazy loading,Mapping entities to console output


âœ… Use Case 2: Book Tickets (Atomic Transaction)
Customer books multiple seats at once.
Steps:
1. Select show_id and seats.
2. Check seat availability.
3. Start transaction â†’ lock seats â†’ update to BOOKED â†’ create booking.
4. Commit on success, rollback on failure.
ğŸ§  JDBC Concepts: Transactions, locking, batch updates, GeneratedKeys

------------------------------------------------------

ğŸ’³ MODULE 3: PAYMENT & CANCELLATION
-----------------------------------
ğŸ¯ Objective:
Simulate payment confirmation and allow cancellation before show time.

ğŸ§± Tables:
- payments(id, booking_id, amount, method, status, txn_ref, paid_at)

âœ… Use Case 1: Payment Confirmation
Simulate a payment after booking.
Steps:
1. Choose payment method (Cash/Card/UPI).
2. Create payment record with status='SUCCESS'.
3. Update booking status to CONFIRMED.
ğŸ§  JDBC Concepts: UPDATE, transaction consistency

âœ… Use Case 2: Cancel Booking
Cancel confirmed bookings before show time.
Steps:
1. Enter booking ID.
2. Validate timing (â‰¥2 hours before show).
3. Start transaction â†’ set booking CANCELLED â†’ free seats â†’ mark REFUND_PENDING.
ğŸ§  JDBC Concepts: Conditional queries, UPDATE, rollback, date comparison

